-- Riddhi Siddhi Gluco Surges to Record in Mumbai as Profit Jumps Six Fold
-- Rajhkumar K Shaaw
-- 2010-07-23T04:33:14Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-23/riddhi-siddhi-gluco-surges-to-record-in-munbai-as-profit-jumps-six-fold.html

          
          
              Riddhi Siddhi Gluco Biols Ltd., an
Indian starch maker, jumped to a record in Mumbai trading after
saying first-quarter profit surged six fold.  
 Riddhi Siddhi soared as much as 20 percent, or by its daily
limit, and traded at 330 rupees as of 9:51 a.m. local time. The
shares are poised for their highest close since they were listed
in June 1994.  
 Net income rose to 311.7 million rupees ($6.6 million) in
the three months ended June 30 from 51.4 million rupees a year
earlier, according to a statement sent to the Bombay Stock
Exchange yesterday.  
